 his cloak in two and given half to a beggar. The name was also borne by five popes, including one who defended Roman Catholic dogma against Eastern Orthodox theology. He died after suffering imprisonment and privations in Naxos and public humiliation in Constantinople, and was promptly acclaimed a martyr by supporters of the Roman Church. Among Protestants, the name is sometimes bestowed in honour of the German theologian  Martin Luther  (  1483–1546 ); <i>Martin</i> was used as a symbolic name for the Protestant Church in satires by both Dryden and Swift. A further influence may be its use as the given name of the civil-rights leader  Martin Luther King  (  1929–68 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Martyn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Martin ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Martin Fishacre was born about 1186, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. He married Isabel Wadeton before 1217. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1186–":"umbes 1186–Surnud","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1186–Male":"1186–Surnud","Abt 1186":"umbes 1186","1215":"1215","Abt 1220":"umbes 1220","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1186":"1186","before 1217":"enne 1217",", , Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1186–":"noin 1186–Kuollut","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1215–Male":"1215–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1186–Male":"1186–Kuollut","Abt 1186":"noin 1186","1215":"1215","Abt 1220":"noin 1220","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1186":"1186","before 1217":"ennen vuotta 1217",", , Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1186–":"environ 1186–Décédé","1187–Female":"1187–Décédée","1215–Male":"1215–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1186–Male":"1186–Décédé","Abt 1186":"environ 1186","1215":"1215","Abt 1220":"environ 1220","1220":"122